Bhopal / A young man going for Iftari was shot in the chest; The miscreant took himself to the hospital, both the accused arrested

The incident took place near the toll mosque of Bhopal.

Youth dies in ICU of private hospital in front of DIG

After the incident, the accused along with his companion himself took the blood-soaked youth to the hospital on a scooter.

Dainik Bhaskar

Jun 01, 2019, 01:20 PM IST

Bhopal. An old scoundrel shot and killed a denter near the toll wali mosque. The incident spread panic in the area. At that time the young man was going for Roza and Iftari. After the incident, the accused along with his companion himself took the blood-soaked youth to the hospital on a scooter and then fled away.

read this also
Wednesday is the hottest day of the season in Bhopal; Temperature crosses 44.2 degrees, state in grip of heat wave

The DIG, who was going for Roza Iftari nearby, also reached the hospital. The young man died in the ICU in front of the DIG. Talaiya police is currently searching for the accused.
Bullet fired during conversation
Mohammad Qasim, 22, resident of Budhwara, used to work in denting and painting. DIG Irshad Wali said that around 7 pm on Friday evening, Qasim was going to an Iftar function near the Toll Wali Mosque. On the way he met Umar and Farooq. During the conversation, a bullet was fired from Umar, which hit Qasim in the chest.
According to the police, a CCTV footage of the incident has surfaced. This incident seems to be happening in this. After being shot, Umar and Farooq took Qasim on a scooter to a nearby private hospital. After this both of them absconded. At present the police is searching for both of them. Only after this the reason for the incident will be revealed. It is learned that there was an argument between Umar and Qasim some time ago regarding denting of a vehicle.
